OL,3,CMajor hospital contractors recorded
OL,4,C#136 million in losses since 2022
OL,6,FThe company Jersey's Government has
OL,7,Fchosen to construct its new hospital
OL,8,Fhas incurred losses totalling #136
OL,9,Fmillion since 2022.
OL,11,FThe accounts for Bouygues UK have been
OL,12,Fin the public realm since September,
OL,13,Fbut they were still chosen as the
OL,14,Fpreferred partner for the new acute
OL,15,Fhospital at Overdale.
OL,17,FThe subsidiary of the French company
OL,18,FBouygues Construction has worked on
OL,19,Fmore than 400 healthcare facilities
OL,20,Fworldwide, including Barnet and
OL,21,FBroomfield Hospital.
